Looks like like the API changed in Bamboo 3.1 and when you try to release, the following error is thrown;

{code}

Caused by: java.lang.NoSuchMethodError: com.atlassian.bamboo.plan.PlanExecutionManager.startManualExecution(Lcom/atlassian/bamboo/plan/Plan;Lcom/atlassian/user/User;Ljava/util/Map;)Lcom/atlassian/bamboo/plan/ExecutionRequestResult;
at com.sysbliss.bamboo.plugins.brmp.action.ViewJiraVersions.doReleaseBuild(ViewJiraVersions.java:85)
... 152 more{code}

Since Bamboo 3.1, when an Ant task runs, the "Path" environment variable get rewritten as:
{code}
PATH=<Java bin path>;<contents of the %Path% variable>
{code}

The problem is that this creates *two* versions of the "Path" variable (Path and PATH), which causes problems with some Windows executables (suc as WSPBuilder.exe) run from the Ant script.

The Path variable should be rewritten as "Path" instead.

Currently we will always look up the depot mapping to use for change detection because we can't guarentee the client stuff will work on the server (e.g. the plans may usually build on a remote agent).  However, by doing this, we lose the ability to handle perforce overlay mappings.  i.e.

{code}
//depot/stuff/...  //client/stuff/...
+ //depot/other/... //client/stuff/other/...
{code}

If we add an option to always use the client side of the mapping rather than doing the look up, we might be able to work around the limitations and customers who *can* use the client on the server can also use overlay mappings.

